## Article 1: General Provisions
1.1 The source code of the Game publicly available on platforms such as GitHub may only be used for **viewing, learning, and compiling to generate executable files for personal entertainment purposes**.
1.2 The terms "User-Generated Content" or "MOD" in this agreement refer to additional content created by users or third parties independently of the Game's core code, using the publicly available application programming interfaces (APIs), scripting systems, or modding development kits provided by the Official.

## Article 2: Rights and Restrictions
2.1 **Grant of License**: The Official grants you a personal, non-transferable, and non-exclusive license to use the Game.
2.2 **Strictly Prohibited Actions**: You **shall not** perform the following actions regarding the Game:
    a) Modify, decompile, crack, or create derivative works based on the core source code or resource files provided by the Official;
    b) Use the Game or any core part for commercial purposes, including but not limited to sale, rental, licensing, or commercial operation, unless written authorization has been obtained from the Official;
    c) Remove any copyright notices, trademarks, or other proprietary rights notices from the Game.

## Article 3: User-Generated Content
3.1 The Official encourages users to create and share MODs within the framework of this agreement and the "User-Generated Content (MOD) Guidelines".
3.2 MODs are content independently created by users, and their authors bear full responsibility for the content. The Official is not responsible for the content, quality, stability, or legality of any third-party MODs.
3.3 The creation and distribution of MODs must fully comply with the separately published "User-Generated Content (MOD) Guidelines" by the Official.

## Article 4: Liability and Disclaimer
4.1 You shall bear full compensation liability for any damages caused to the Official or third parties due to your violation of this agreement or the "User-Generated Content (MOD) Guidelines".

## Article 5: Miscellaneous
5.1 The Official reserves the right to modify the terms of this agreement at any time. The modified agreement will be published in the same location. If you do not agree with the modifications, you should immediately stop using the Game.
5.2 The conclusion, execution, and interpretation of this agreement and the resolution of disputes shall be governed by the laws of the People's Republic of China.

